JOHANNESBURG – The Auditor-General (AG)’s office has reportedly withdrawn its team from the eThekwini Municipality after its auditors there received death threats, The Mercury reported on Friday. The AG’s KZN office has apparently written to the city informing it of the immediate withdrawal of the auditors. WATCH: Irregular expenditure in municipalities up 75% Apparently, some staff members received threatening phone calls after asking for supply chain management documents. This move comes amid concerns from the Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu that his audit teams are working in increasingly hostile environments. Makwetu said there have been increased push-backs from public officials on audit findings. The report comes a day after Makwetu released the municipal financial audits of the past financial year which showed out of 257 municipalities audited only 33 received clean audits. eNCA